{"ts":"2026-06-27T04:41:10.662Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Considering Design Direction**\n\nI'm now exploring the potential of utilizing `DataTable` side drawers to display detailed information. I'm also investigating if we can tailor `/portal/billing` and `/portal/billing/invoices` into a high-fidelity corporate finance portal specifically for GFF AI. I've begun to review the current user design.\n\n\n**Crafting a Design Plan**\n\nI'm starting to build a concise internal design plan for the Client Portal Billing and Invoices system. I'm focusing on crafting a compelling narrative—a story for the CFO or Enterprise Administrator. The design aims for absolute clarity on sovereign AI spend. I am now working on a short internal design plan. It is now focused on the page or section narrative. I will move on to the next points after that is completed.\n\n\n**Defining the UI Narrative**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the initial user experience. I envision a financial cockpit: a clean, high-end display showcasing crucial data points like total spend, active contracts, and payment cycles. The design emphasizes clarity with a high-contrast Invoice Ledger, all underpinned by GFF AI's signature security and premium aesthetic. I also am visualizing a metaphor for the interface, calling it The Sovereign Ledger, with security enclaves and cryptographic seals.\n\n\n**Visualizing Secure Synchronization**\n\nI'm now creating SVG diagrams to illustrate secure ledger certificate synchronization. These diagrams will visually represent the process between the client enclave and GFF's Central Treasury. I'm focusing on clarity and precision in these visual representations, ensuring that the process is easily understood at a glance. I am also working on how to create the layout strategy.\n\n**Developing Layout Strategy**\n\nI've moved on to the layout strategy. The design for `/portal/billing` will be a billing overview, featuring a cryptographic \"Sovereign Financial Agreement\" certification badge, dynamic billing indicators, and contract specifications. I'm prioritizing interactive metrics and a bespoke billing contact card, aiming for a premium and user-friendly experience.\n\n\n**Refining Interactive Elements**\n\nI'm now focusing on interactive elements, specifically for the invoice ledger. I'm prioritizing breadcrumb navigation and a dedicated title with key stats. I'm developing a multi-filter ledger table with actionable items like \"View Invoice Preview\" and \"Contact Finance.\" The plan also includes a dynamic detail modal for each invoice, displaying line items with key actions. I also want swift portal ticket escalation.\n\n\n**Implementing Interactive Details**\n\nI'm now focusing on adding interactive details. I plan to incorporate a \"verify\" button that showcases a live, terminal-style cryptographic seal trace. I'm also planning to create a modal or side drawer that displays a premium invoice preview with line items, computing hour breakdown, signature, and project associations. I am also working on an animated copy button and a custom quick-contact panel to trigger message states.\n\nI'm also working on mobile strategy. I plan to use CSS Grid to collapse 3-column metric grids to a 1-column stack and convert data tables to premium mobile cards. I'm focused on clean padding and accessible tap targets.\n\n\n**Prioritizing UI Enhancement**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on re-engineering `/portal/billing` and `/portal/billing/invoices` to match the premium design. Specifically, I plan to create a financial cockpit UI, rich stats, cryptographic interactions, and \"Contact GFF Treasury\" support in the billing page. I also intend to refine the invoices table list with high-fidelity filtering, status selection, mobile layouts, and interactive previews.\n\n\n**Integrating Custom Components**\n\nI'm now focusing on implementing custom high-end UI components directly within the billing page files to ensure total control over user experience and layout. I'm reviewing the `previewInvoices` interface, and I plan to include project associations by mapping invoice IDs to related projects. I'm incorporating billing summary, invoice status, due date, amount preview, and a billing contact card, per the request.\n\n\n**Tracing Billing Interactions**\n\nI'm now tracing the interaction between the billing pages and key components. I'm focusing on `/portal/billing` and envision a highly customized design. I've begun to list out key sections like the Dynamic Top Metrics Dashboard with a bento layout for metrics, and core allocations. I'm prioritizing the display of \"Sovereign Plan Parameters\", and a financial summary card with billed, paid, and unpaid amounts.\n\n\n"}}
